BETTS, Fk. (48, no occupation); 

feloniously shooting at 



   Thomas Jabez Wood, with intent to commit murder; feloniously wounding the said Wood with intent to commit murder.







                     WILLIAMS, George (55, coachman); 





                     MACKRILL, Alfred (27, labourer); 





                     SMITH, William (26, labourer); 





                     BROOKS, Charles (22, labourer); Smith and Brooks 

                     being found by night having in their possession, without lawful excuse, certain implements of house-break
ing; Smith and Williams 

                     burglary in the dwelling-house of 



                        John Compston and stealing therein two overcoats and other articles, the property of the said John Compston; Mackrill 

                     feloniously receiving one of the said overcoats well knowing it to have been stolen. Smith 

                     pleaded guilty of the burglary; 


                     Brooks of being in possession of housebreaking implements.
